Make the whole app responsive on mobile

Adds the one architectural piece needed for mobile — a slide-in
sidebar drawer behind a hamburger button — and walks every page
collapsing its multi-column layouts to a single column on small
screens.

Platform shell
  - New PlatformShell client wrapper renders a mobile-only header
    bar (hamburger + logo) for screens below lg, and gates the
    sidebar behind translate transforms so it slides in from the
    left when toggled.
  - Backdrop click + Escape + route change all close the drawer;
    body scroll is locked while it's open.
  - Sidebar gains a close button on mobile, larger touch targets
    on nav items, and is sticky 280px on lg+.
  - Adds a viewport export to the root layout so iOS phones don't
    auto-scale the page.

Page topbars
  - Search inputs flex to a full-width second row on mobile.
  - Non-essential icon buttons (notifications, share, pin) are
    hidden below sm.
  - Primary CTAs ("Start a project", "Claim a step", "Modify
    project") shorten to "Start" / "Claim" / "Modify" on small
    screens.
  - Padding reduces from px-10 py-5 to px-4 py-4 on mobile.

Page bodies
  - Dashboard pinned + suggested grids: 1-col → 2-col → 3-col.
    Greeting + stats stack vertically on mobile.
  - Browse projects: filters become a "Show filters" toggle on
    mobile that reveals the panel above the results; the cards
    grid drops to a single column.
  - My projects: card grid 1 → 2 cols; list rows stack
    vertically with the grid columns becoming flex children.
  - Project view: cover padding and headline scale down; body
    grid drops to a single column with the right rail flowing
    below the steps; rail loses its sticky on small.
  - Profile: TOC becomes a horizontal pill row above the form
    sections; the skills table 4-col grid stacks vertically with
    a labelled "Match me" toggle and a full-width Remove button.
  - Create/Edit project: step rows reflow so the skill picker
    drops to a second row beneath the title/description on
    mobile, with the remove button sitting top-right.

Marketing homepage
  - Navbar collapses: nav links hidden under lg, "Sign in" hidden
    under sm so the button row fits on a phone.
  - All sections lose the bigger px-8 / py-20 padding for a snug
    px-4 / py-12 mobile treatment.
  - Hero gap shrinks from gap-16 to gap-10 on mobile.

p-10 page padding becomes p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-10 across the platform.
